3971 // The class IntVar is a subset of IntExpr. In addition to the
3972 // IntExpr protocol, it offers persistence, removing values from the domains,
3973 // and a finer model for events.
3974 class IntVar : public IntExpr {
3975  public:
3976  explicit IntVar(Solver* const s);
3977  IntVar(Solver* const s, const std::string& name);
3978  ~IntVar() override {}
3979 
3980  bool IsVar() const override { return true; }
3981  IntVar* Var() override { return this; }
3982 
3983  // This method returns the value of the variable. This method checks
3984  // before that the variable is bound.
3985  virtual int64 Value() const = 0;
3986 
3987  // This method removes the value 'v' from the domain of the variable.
3988  virtual void RemoveValue(int64 v) = 0;
3989 
3990  // This method removes the interval 'l' .. 'u' from the domain of
3991  // the variable. It assumes that 'l' <= 'u'.
3992  virtual void RemoveInterval(int64 l, int64 u) = 0;
3993 
3994  // This method remove the values from the domain of the variable.
3995  virtual void RemoveValues(const std::vector<int64>& values);
3996 
3997  // This method intersects the current domain with the values in the array.
3998  virtual void SetValues(const std::vector<int64>& values);
3999 
4000  // This method attaches a demon that will be awakened when the
4001  // variable is bound.
4002  virtual void WhenBound(Demon* d) = 0;
4003  // This method attaches a closure that will be awakened when the
4004  // variable is bound.
4005  void WhenBound(Solver::Closure closure) {
4006  WhenBound(solver()->MakeClosureDemon(std::move(closure)));
4007  }
4008 
4009 #if !defined(SWIG)
4010  // This method attaches an action that will be awakened when the
4011  // variable is bound.
4012  void WhenBound(Solver::Action action) {
4013  WhenBound(solver()->MakeActionDemon(std::move(action)));
4014  }
4015 #endif // SWIG
4016 
4017  // This method attaches a demon that will watch any domain
4018  // modification of the domain of the variable.
4019  virtual void WhenDomain(Demon* d) = 0;
4020  // This method attaches a closure that will watch any domain
4021  // modification of the domain of the variable.
4022  void WhenDomain(Solver::Closure closure) {
4023  WhenDomain(solver()->MakeClosureDemon(std::move(closure)));
4024  }
4025 #if !defined(SWIG)
4026  // This method attaches an action that will watch any domain
4027  // modification of the domain of the variable.
4028  void WhenDomain(Solver::Action action) {
4029  WhenDomain(solver()->MakeActionDemon(std::move(action)));
4030  }
4031 #endif // SWIG
4032 
4033  // This method returns the number of values in the domain of the variable.
4034  virtual uint64 Size() const = 0;
4035 
4036  // This method returns whether the value 'v' is in the domain of the variable.
4037  virtual bool Contains(int64 v) const = 0;
4038 
4039  // Creates a hole iterator. When 'reversible' is false, the returned
4040  // object is created on the normal C++ heap and the solver does NOT
4041  // take ownership of the object.
4042  virtual IntVarIterator* MakeHoleIterator(bool reversible) const = 0;
4043 
4044  // Creates a domain iterator. When 'reversible' is false, the
4045  // returned object is created on the normal C++ heap and the solver
4046  // does NOT take ownership of the object.
4047  virtual IntVarIterator* MakeDomainIterator(bool reversible) const = 0;
4048 
4049  // Returns the previous min.
4050  virtual int64 OldMin() const = 0;
4051 
4052  // Returns the previous max.
4053  virtual int64 OldMax() const = 0;
4054 
4055  virtual int VarType() const;
4056 
4057  // Accepts the given visitor.
4058  void Accept(ModelVisitor* const visitor) const override;
4059 
4060  // IsEqual
4061  virtual IntVar* IsEqual(int64 constant) = 0;
4062  virtual IntVar* IsDifferent(int64 constant) = 0;
4063  virtual IntVar* IsGreaterOrEqual(int64 constant) = 0;
4064  virtual IntVar* IsLessOrEqual(int64 constant) = 0;
4065 
4066  // Returns the index of the variable.
4067  int index() const { return index_; }
4068 
4069  private:

4071  DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(IntVar);
4072 };

4218 // ---------- Search Limits ----------
4219 
4220 // Base class of all search limits.
4221 class SearchLimit : public SearchMonitor {
4222  public:
4223  explicit SearchLimit(Solver* const s) : SearchMonitor(s), crossed_(false) {}
4224  ~SearchLimit() override;
4225 
4226  // Returns true if the limit has been crossed.
4227  bool crossed() const { return crossed_; }
4228 
4229  // This method is called to check the status of the limit. A return
4230  // value of true indicates that we have indeed crossed the limit. In
4231  // that case, this method will not be called again and the remaining
4232  // search will be discarded.
4233  virtual bool Check() = 0;
4234 
4235  // This method is called when the search limit is initialized.
4236  virtual void Init() = 0;
4237 
4238  // Copy a limit. Warning: leads to a direct (no check) downcasting of 'limit'
4239  // so one needs to be sure both SearchLimits are of the same type.
4240  virtual void Copy(const SearchLimit* const limit) = 0;
4241 
4242  // Allocates a clone of the limit.
4243  virtual SearchLimit* MakeClone() const = 0;
4244 
4245  // Internal methods.
4246  void EnterSearch() override;
4247  void BeginNextDecision(DecisionBuilder* const b) override;
4248  void PeriodicCheck() override;
4249  void RefuteDecision(Decision* const d) override;
4250  std::string DebugString() const override {
4251  return absl::StrFormat("SearchLimit(crossed = %i)", crossed_);
4252  }
4253 
4254  private:
4255  void TopPeriodicCheck();
4256 
4257  bool crossed_;
4258  DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(SearchLimit);
4259 };

4277  int64 solutions);
4278  absl::Duration duration_limit() const { return duration_limit_; }
4279  int64 wall_time() const {
4280  return duration_limit_ == absl::InfiniteDuration()
4281  ? kint64max
4282  : absl::ToInt64Milliseconds(duration_limit());
4283  }

4285  int64 failures() const { return failures_; }

4293  }

4296 
4297  private:
4298  bool CheckTime();
4299  absl::Duration TimeElapsed();
4300  static int64 GetPercent(int64 value, int64 offset, int64 total) {
4301  return (total > 0 && total < kint64max) ? 100 * (value - offset) / total
4302  : -1;
4303  }

4313  int64 failures_;
4314  int64 failures_offset_;
4315  int64 solutions_;
4316  int64 solutions_offset_;
4317  // If cumulative if false, then the limit applies to each search
4318  // independently. If it's true, the limit applies globally to all search for
4319  // which this monitor is used.
4320  // When cumulative is true, the offset fields have two different meanings
4321  // depending on context:
4322  // - within a search, it's an offset to be subtracted from the current value

4327 // ---------- Interval Var ----------
4328 
4329 // Interval variables are often used in scheduling. The main characteristics
4330 // of an IntervalVar are the start position, duration, and end
4331 // date. All these characteristics can be queried and set, and demons can
4332 // be posted on their modifications.
4333 //
4334 // An important aspect is optionality: an IntervalVar can be performed or not.
4335 // If unperformed, then it simply does not exist, and its characteristics
4336 // cannot be accessed any more. An interval var is automatically marked
4337 // as unperformed when it is not consistent anymore (start greater
4338 // than end, duration < 0...)
4339 class IntervalVar : public PropagationBaseObject {
4340  public:
4341  // The smallest acceptable value to be returned by StartMin()
4342  static const int64 kMinValidValue;
4343  // The largest acceptable value to be returned by EndMax()
4344  static const int64 kMaxValidValue;
4345  IntervalVar(Solver* const solver, const std::string& name)
4346  : PropagationBaseObject(solver) {
4347  set_name(name);
4348  }
4349  ~IntervalVar() override {}
4350 
4351  // These methods query, set, and watch the start position of the
4352  // interval var.
4353  virtual int64 StartMin() const = 0;
4354  virtual int64 StartMax() const = 0;
4355  virtual void SetStartMin(int64 m) = 0;
4356  virtual void SetStartMax(int64 m) = 0;
4357  virtual void SetStartRange(int64 mi, int64 ma) = 0;
4358  virtual int64 OldStartMin() const = 0;
4359  virtual int64 OldStartMax() const = 0;
4360  virtual void WhenStartRange(Demon* const d) = 0;
4361  void WhenStartRange(Solver::Closure closure) {
4362  WhenStartRange(solver()->MakeClosureDemon(std::move(closure)));
4363  }
4364 #if !defined(SWIG)
4365  void WhenStartRange(Solver::Action action) {
4366  WhenStartRange(solver()->MakeActionDemon(std::move(action)));
4367  }
4368 #endif // SWIG
4369  virtual void WhenStartBound(Demon* const d) = 0;
4370  void WhenStartBound(Solver::Closure closure) {
4371  WhenStartBound(solver()->MakeClosureDemon(std::move(closure)));
4372  }
4373 #if !defined(SWIG)
4374  void WhenStartBound(Solver::Action action) {
4375  WhenStartBound(solver()->MakeActionDemon(std::move(action)));
4376  }
4377 #endif // SWIG
4378 
4379  // These methods query, set, and watch the duration of the interval var.
4380  virtual int64 DurationMin() const = 0;
4381  virtual int64 DurationMax() const = 0;
4382  virtual void SetDurationMin(int64 m) = 0;
4383  virtual void SetDurationMax(int64 m) = 0;
4384  virtual void SetDurationRange(int64 mi, int64 ma) = 0;

4393  WhenDurationRange(solver()->MakeActionDemon(std::move(action)));
4394  }

4396  virtual void WhenDurationBound(Demon* const d) = 0;
4397  void WhenDurationBound(Solver::Closure closure) {
4398  WhenDurationBound(solver()->MakeClosureDemon(std::move(closure)));
4399  }
4400 #if !defined(SWIG)
4401  void WhenDurationBound(Solver::Action action) {
4402  WhenDurationBound(solver()->MakeActionDemon(std::move(action)));
4403  }
4404 #endif // SWIG
4405

4408  virtual int64 EndMax() const = 0;

4421  }

4450  }

4456  void WhenAnything(Solver::Closure closure) {
4457  WhenAnything(solver()->MakeClosureDemon(std::move(closure)));
4458  }
4459 #if !defined(SWIG)

4463  }
4464 #endif // SWIG

4468  // be used if the interval var is unperformed.
4469  virtual IntExpr* StartExpr() = 0;
4470  virtual IntExpr* DurationExpr() = 0;
4471  virtual IntExpr* EndExpr() = 0;
4472  virtual IntExpr* PerformedExpr() = 0;
4473  // These methods create expressions encapsulating the start, end
4474  // and duration of the interval var. If the interval var is
4475  // unperformed, they will return the unperformed_value.
4476  virtual IntExpr* SafeStartExpr(int64 unperformed_value) = 0;
4477  virtual IntExpr* SafeDurationExpr(int64 unperformed_value) = 0;
4478  virtual IntExpr* SafeEndExpr(int64 unperformed_value) = 0;
4479

4486 
4487 // ----- SequenceVar -----
4488 
4489 // A sequence variable is a variable whose domain is a set of possible
4490 // orderings of the interval variables. It allows ordering of tasks. It
4491 // has two sets of methods: ComputePossibleFirstsAndLasts(), which
4492 // returns the list of interval variables that can be ranked first or
4493 // last; and RankFirst/RankNotFirst/RankLast/RankNotLast, which can be
4494 // used to create the search decision.
4495 class SequenceVar : public PropagationBaseObject {
4496  public:
4497  SequenceVar(Solver* const s, const std::vector<IntervalVar*>& intervals,
4498  const std::vector<IntVar*>& nexts, const std::string& name);
4499 
4500  ~SequenceVar() override;
4501 
4502  std::string DebugString() const override;
4503 
4504 #if !defined(SWIG)
4505  // Returns the minimum and maximum duration of combined interval
4506  // vars in the sequence.
4507  void DurationRange(int64* const dmin, int64* const dmax) const;
4508 
4509  // Returns the minimum start min and the maximum end max of all
4510  // interval vars in the sequence.
4511  void HorizonRange(int64* const hmin, int64* const hmax) const;
4512 
4513  // Returns the minimum start min and the maximum end max of all
4514  // unranked interval vars in the sequence.
4515  void ActiveHorizonRange(int64* const hmin, int64* const hmax) const;
4516 
4517  // Compute statistics on the sequence.
4518  void ComputeStatistics(int* const ranked, int* const not_ranked,
4519  int* const unperformed) const;
4520 #endif // !defined(SWIG)
4521 
4522  // Ranks the index_th interval var first of all unranked interval
4523  // vars. After that, it will no longer be considered ranked.
4524  void RankFirst(int index);
4525 
4526  // Indicates that the index_th interval var will not be ranked first
4527  // of all currently unranked interval vars.
4528  void RankNotFirst(int index);
4529 
4530  // Ranks the index_th interval var first of all unranked interval
4531  // vars. After that, it will no longer be considered ranked.
4532  void RankLast(int index);
4533 
4534  // Indicates that the index_th interval var will not be ranked first
4535  // of all currently unranked interval vars.
4536  void RankNotLast(int index);
4537 
4538  // Computes the set of indices of interval variables that can be
4539  // ranked first in the set of unranked activities.
4540  void ComputePossibleFirstsAndLasts(std::vector<int>* const possible_firsts,
4541  std::vector<int>* const possible_lasts);
4542 
4543  // Applies the following sequence of ranks, ranks first, then rank
4544  // last. rank_first and rank_last represents different directions.
4545  // rank_first[0] corresponds to the first interval of the sequence.
4546  // rank_last[0] corresponds to the last interval of the sequence.
4547  // All intervals in the unperformed vector will be marked as such.
4548  void RankSequence(const std::vector<int>& rank_first,
4549  const std::vector<int>& rank_last,
4550  const std::vector<int>& unperformed);
4551 
4552  // Clears 'rank_first' and 'rank_last', and fills them with the
4553  // intervals in the order of the ranks. If all variables are ranked,
4554  // 'rank_first' will contain all variables, and 'rank_last' will
4555  // contain none.
4556  // 'unperformed' will contains all such interval variables.
4557  // rank_first and rank_last represents different directions.
4558  // rank_first[0] corresponds to the first interval of the sequence.
4559  // rank_last[0] corresponds to the last interval of the sequence.
4560  void FillSequence(std::vector<int>* const rank_first,
4561  std::vector<int>* const rank_last,
4562  std::vector<int>* const unperformed) const;
4563 
4564  // Returns the index_th interval of the sequence.
4565  IntervalVar* Interval(int index) const;
4566 
4567  // Returns the next of the index_th interval of the sequence.
4568  IntVar* Next(int index) const;
4569 
4570  // Returns the number of interval vars in the sequence.
4571  int64 size() const { return intervals_.size(); }
4572 
4573  // Accepts the given visitor.
4574  virtual void Accept(ModelVisitor* const visitor) const;
4575 
4576  private:

4579  void UpdatePrevious() const;
4580 
4581  const std::vector<IntervalVar*> intervals_;
4582  const std::vector<IntVar*> nexts_;
4583  mutable std::vector<int> previous_;
4584 };

4759 // ----- SequenceVarElement -----
4760 
4761 // The SequenceVarElement stores a partial representation of ranked
4762 // interval variables in the underlying sequence variable.
4763 // This representation consists of three vectors:
4764 // - the forward sequence. That is the list of interval variables
4765 // ranked first in the sequence. The first element of the backward
4766 // sequence is the first interval in the sequence variable.
4767 // - the backward sequence. That is the list of interval variables
4768 // ranked last in the sequence. The first element of the backward
4769 // sequence is the last interval in the sequence variable.
4770 // - The list of unperformed interval variables.
4771 // Furthermore, if all performed variables are ranked, then by
4772 // convention, the forward_sequence will contain all such variables
4773 // and the backward_sequence will be empty.
4774 class SequenceVarElement : public AssignmentElement {
4775  public:
4776  SequenceVarElement();
4777  explicit SequenceVarElement(SequenceVar* const var);
4778  void Reset(SequenceVar* const var);
4779  SequenceVarElement* Clone();
4780  void Copy(const SequenceVarElement& element);
4781  SequenceVar* Var() const { return var_; }
4782  void Store();
4783  void Restore();
4784  void LoadFromProto(
4785  const SequenceVarAssignment& sequence_var_assignment_proto);
4786  void WriteToProto(SequenceVarAssignment* sequence_var_assignment_proto) const;
4787 
4788  const std::vector<int>& ForwardSequence() const;
4789  const std::vector<int>& BackwardSequence() const;
4790  const std::vector<int>& Unperformed() const;
4791  void SetSequence(const std::vector<int>& forward_sequence,
4792  const std::vector<int>& backward_sequence,
4793  const std::vector<int>& unperformed);
4794  void SetForwardSequence(const std::vector<int>& forward_sequence);
4795  void SetBackwardSequence(const std::vector<int>& backward_sequence);
4796  void SetUnperformed(const std::vector<int>& unperformed);
4797  bool Bound() const {
4798  return forward_sequence_.size() + unperformed_.size() == var_->size();
4799  }
4800 
4801  std::string DebugString() const;
4802 
4803  bool operator==(const SequenceVarElement& element) const;
4804  bool operator!=(const SequenceVarElement& element) const {
4805  return !(*this == element);
4806  }
4807 
4808  private:
4809  bool CheckClassInvariants();
4810 
4811  SequenceVar* var_;
4812  std::vector<int> forward_sequence_;
4813  std::vector<int> backward_sequence_;
4814  std::vector<int> unperformed_;
4815 };
4816 
4817 // ----- Assignment element container -----
4818 
4819 template <class V, class E>
4820 class AssignmentContainer {
4821  public:
4822  AssignmentContainer() {}
4823  E* Add(V* var) {
4824  CHECK(var != nullptr);
4825  int index = -1;
4826  if (!Find(var, &index)) {
4827  return FastAdd(var);
4828  } else {
4829  return &elements_[index];
4830  }
4831  }
4832  // Adds element without checking its presence in the container.
4833  E* FastAdd(V* var) {
4834  DCHECK(var != nullptr);
4835  elements_.emplace_back(var);
4836  return &elements_.back();
4837  }
4838  // Advanced usage: Adds element at a given position; position has to have
4839  // been allocated with AssignmentContainer::Resize() beforehand.
4840  E* AddAtPosition(V* var, int position) {
4841  elements_[position].Reset(var);
4842  return &elements_[position];
4843  }
4844  void Clear() {
4845  elements_.clear();
4846  if (!elements_map_.empty()) { // 2x speedup on OR-tools.
4847  elements_map_.clear();
4848  }
4849  }
4850  // Advanced usage: Resizes the container, potentially adding elements with
4851  // null variables.
4852  void Resize(size_t size) { elements_.resize(size); }
4853  bool Empty() const { return elements_.empty(); }
4854  // Copies the elements of 'container' which are already in the calling
4855  // container.
4856  void CopyIntersection(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) {
4857  for (int i = 0; i < container.elements_.size(); ++i) {
4858  const E& element = container.elements_[i];
4859  const V* const var = element.Var();
4860  int index = -1;
4861  if (i < elements_.size() && elements_[i].Var() == var) {
4862  index = i;
4863  } else if (!Find(var, &index)) {
4864  continue;
4865  }
4866  DCHECK_GE(index, 0);
4867  E* const local_element = &elements_[index];
4868  local_element->Copy(element);
4869  if (element.Activated()) {
4870  local_element->Activate();
4871  } else {
4872  local_element->Deactivate();
4873  }
4874  }
4875  }
4876  // Copies all the elements of 'container' to this container, clearing its
4877  // previous content.
4878  void Copy(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) {
4879  Clear();
4880  for (int i = 0; i < container.elements_.size(); ++i) {
4881  const E& element = container.elements_[i];
4882  FastAdd(element.Var())->Copy(element);
4883  }
4884  }
4885  bool Contains(const V* const var) const {
4886  int index;
4887  return Find(var, &index);
4888  }
4889  E* MutableElement(const V* const var) {
4890  E* const element = MutableElementOrNull(var);
4891  DCHECK(element != nullptr)
4892  << "Unknown variable " << var->DebugString() << " in solution";
4893  return element;
4894  }
4895  E* MutableElementOrNull(const V* const var) {
4896  int index = -1;
4897  if (Find(var, &index)) {
4898  return MutableElement(index);
4899  }
4900  return nullptr;
4901  }
4902  const E& Element(const V* const var) const {
4903  const E* const element = ElementPtrOrNull(var);
4904  DCHECK(element != nullptr)
4905  << "Unknown variable " << var->DebugString() << " in solution";
4906  return *element;
4907  }
4908  const E* ElementPtrOrNull(const V* const var) const {
4909  int index = -1;
4910  if (Find(var, &index)) {
4911  return &Element(index);
4912  }
4913  return nullptr;
4914  }
4915  const std::vector<E>& elements() const { return elements_; }
4916  E* MutableElement(int index) { return &elements_[index]; }
4917  const E& Element(int index) const { return elements_[index]; }
4918  int Size() const { return elements_.size(); }
4919  void Store() {
4920  for (E& element : elements_) {
4921  element.Store();
4922  }
4923  }
4924  void Restore() {
4925  for (E& element : elements_) {
4926  if (element.Activated()) {
4927  element.Restore();
4928  }
4929  }
4930  }
4931  bool AreAllElementsBound() const {
4932  for (const E& element : elements_) {
4933  if (!element.Bound()) return false;
4934  }
4935  return true;
4936  }
4937 
4938  // Returns true if this and 'container' both represent the same V* -> E map.
4939  // Runs in linear time; requires that the == operator on the type E is well
4940  // defined.
4941  bool operator==(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) const {
4942  // We may not have any work to do
4943  if (Size() != container.Size()) {
4944  return false;
4945  }
4946  // The == should be order-independent
4947  EnsureMapIsUpToDate();
4948  // Do not use the hash_map::== operator! It
4949  // compares both content and how the map is hashed (e.g., number of
4950  // buckets). This is not what we want.
4951  for (const E& element : container.elements_) {
4952  const int position =
4953  gtl::FindWithDefault(elements_map_, element.Var(), -1);
4954  if (position < 0 || elements_[position] != element) {
4955  return false;
4956  }
4957  }
4958  return true;
4959  }
4960  bool operator!=(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) const {
4961  return !(*this == container);
4962  }
4963 
4964  private:
4965  void EnsureMapIsUpToDate() const {
4966  absl::flat_hash_map<const V*, int>* map =
4967  const_cast<absl::flat_hash_map<const V*, int>*>(&elements_map_);
4968  for (int i = map->size(); i < elements_.size(); ++i) {
4969  (*map)[elements_[i].Var()] = i;
4970  }
4971  }
4972  bool Find(const V* const var, int* index) const {
4973  // This threshold was determined from microbenchmarks on Nehalem platform.
4974  const size_t kMaxSizeForLinearAccess = 11;
4975  if (Size() <= kMaxSizeForLinearAccess) {
4976  // Look for 'var' in the container by performing a linear
4977  // search, avoiding the access to (and creation of) the elements
4978  // hash table.
4979  for (int i = 0; i < elements_.size(); ++i) {
4980  if (var == elements_[i].Var()) {
4981  *index = i;
4982  return true;
4983  }
4984  }
4985  return false;
4986  } else {
4987  EnsureMapIsUpToDate();
4988  DCHECK_EQ(elements_map_.size(), elements_.size());
4989  return gtl::FindCopy(elements_map_, var, index);
4990  }
4991  }
4992 
4993  std::vector<E> elements_;
4994  absl::flat_hash_map<const V*, int> elements_map_;
4995 };

4997 // ----- Assignment -----

4999 // An Assignment is a variable -> domains mapping, used
5000 // to report solutions to the user.
5001 class Assignment : public PropagationBaseObject {

5007  SequenceContainer;

5016  sequence_var_container_.Empty();

5020  }

5181  DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(Assignment);
5182 };
5183 
5184 std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& out,
5185  const Assignment& assignment); // NOLINT
5186 
5187 // Given a "source_assignment", clears the "target_assignment" and adds
5188 // all IntVars in "target_vars", with the values of the variables set according
5189 // to the corresponding values of "source_vars" in "source_assignment".
5190 // source_vars and target_vars must have the same number of elements.
5191 // The source and target assignments can belong to different Solvers.
5192 void SetAssignmentFromAssignment(Assignment* target_assignment,
5193  const std::vector<IntVar*>& target_vars,
5194  const Assignment* source_assignment,
5195  const std::vector<IntVar*>& source_vars);
5196 
5197 // ---------- Pack Constraint ----------
5198 
5199 class Pack : public Constraint {
5200  public:
5201  Pack(Solver* const s, const std::vector<IntVar*>& vars, int number_of_bins);
5202 
5203  ~Pack() override;
5204 
5205  // ----- Public API -----
5206 
5207  // Dimensions are additional constraints than can restrict what is
5208  // possible with the pack constraint. It can be used to set capacity
5209  // limits, to count objects per bin, to compute unassigned
5210  // penalties...
5211 
5212  // This dimension imposes that for all bins b, the weighted sum
5213  // (weights[i]) of all objects i assigned to 'b' is less or equal
5214  // 'bounds[b]'.
5215  void AddWeightedSumLessOrEqualConstantDimension(
5216  const std::vector<int64>& weights, const std::vector<int64>& bounds);
5217 
5218  // This dimension imposes that for all bins b, the weighted sum
5219  // (weights->Run(i)) of all objects i assigned to 'b' is less or
5220  // equal to 'bounds[b]'. Ownership of the callback is transferred to
5221  // the pack constraint.
5222  void AddWeightedSumLessOrEqualConstantDimension(
5223  Solver::IndexEvaluator1 weights, const std::vector<int64>& bounds);
5224 
5225  // This dimension imposes that for all bins b, the weighted sum
5226  // (weights->Run(i, b) of all objects i assigned to 'b' is less or
5227  // equal to 'bounds[b]'. Ownership of the callback is transferred to
5228  // the pack constraint.
5229  void AddWeightedSumLessOrEqualConstantDimension(
5230  Solver::IndexEvaluator2 weights, const std::vector<int64>& bounds);
5231 
5232  // This dimension imposes that for all bins b, the weighted sum
5233  // (weights[i]) of all objects i assigned to 'b' is equal to loads[b].
5234  void AddWeightedSumEqualVarDimension(const std::vector<int64>& weights,
5235  const std::vector<IntVar*>& loads);
5236 
5237  // This dimension imposes that for all bins b, the weighted sum
5238  // (weights->Run(i, b)) of all objects i assigned to 'b' is equal to
5239  // loads[b].
5240  void AddWeightedSumEqualVarDimension(Solver::IndexEvaluator2 weights,
5241  const std::vector<IntVar*>& loads);
5242 
5243  // This dimension imposes:
5244  // forall b in bins,
5245  // sum (i in items: usage[i] * is_assigned(i, b)) <= capacity[b]
5246  // where is_assigned(i, b) is true if and only if item i is assigned
5247  // to the bin b.
5248  //
5249  // This can be used to model shapes of items by linking variables of
5250  // the same item on parallel dimensions with an allowed assignment
5251  // constraint.
5252  void AddSumVariableWeightsLessOrEqualConstantDimension(
5253  const std::vector<IntVar*>& usage, const std::vector<int64>& capacity);
5254 
5255  // This dimension enforces that cost_var == sum of weights[i] for
5256  // all objects 'i' assigned to a bin.
5257  void AddWeightedSumOfAssignedDimension(const std::vector<int64>& weights,
5258  IntVar* const cost_var);
5259 
5260  // This dimension links 'count_var' to the actual number of bins used in the
5261  // pack.
5262  void AddCountUsedBinDimension(IntVar* const count_var);
5263 
5264  // This dimension links 'count_var' to the actual number of items
5265  // assigned to a bin in the pack.
5266  void AddCountAssignedItemsDimension(IntVar* const count_var);
5267  // ----- Internal API -----
5268 
5269  void Post() override;
5270  void ClearAll();
5271  void PropagateDelayed();
5272  void InitialPropagate() override;
5273  void Propagate();
5274  void OneDomain(int var_index);
5275  std::string DebugString() const override;
5276  bool IsUndecided(int var_index, int bin_index) const;
5277  void SetImpossible(int var_index, int bin_index);
5278  void Assign(int var_index, int bin_index);
5279  bool IsAssignedStatusKnown(int var_index) const;
5280  bool IsPossible(int var_index, int bin_index) const;
5281  IntVar* AssignVar(int var_index, int bin_index) const;
5282  void SetAssigned(int var_index);
5283  void SetUnassigned(int var_index);
5284  void RemoveAllPossibleFromBin(int bin_index);
5285  void AssignAllPossibleToBin(int bin_index);
5286  void AssignFirstPossibleToBin(int bin_index);
5287  void AssignAllRemainingItems();
5288  void UnassignAllRemainingItems();
5289  // Accepts the given visitor.
5290  void Accept(ModelVisitor* const visitor) const override;
5291 
5292  private:
5293  bool IsInProcess() const;
5294  const std::vector<IntVar*> vars_;
5295  const int bins_;
5296  std::vector<Dimension*> dims_;
5297  std::unique_ptr<RevBitMatrix> unprocessed_;
5298  std::vector<std::vector<int>> forced_;
5299  std::vector<std::vector<int>> removed_;
5300  std::vector<IntVarIterator*> holes_;
5301  uint64 stamp_;
5302  Demon* demon_;
5303  std::vector<std::pair<int, int>> to_set_;
5304  std::vector<std::pair<int, int>> to_unset_;
5305  bool in_process_;
5306 };
5307 
5308 // ----- Disjunctive Constraint -----
5309 
5310 class DisjunctiveConstraint : public Constraint {
5311  public:
5312  DisjunctiveConstraint(Solver* const s,
5313  const std::vector<IntervalVar*>& intervals,
5314  const std::string& name);
5315  ~DisjunctiveConstraint() override;
5316 
5317  // Creates a sequence variable from the constraint.
5318  virtual SequenceVar* MakeSequenceVar() = 0;
5319 
5320  // Add a transition time between intervals. It forces the distance between
5321  // the end of interval a and start of interval b that follows it to be at
5322  // least transition_time(a, b). This function must always return
5323  // a positive or null value.
5324  void SetTransitionTime(Solver::IndexEvaluator2 transition_time);
5325 
5326  int64 TransitionTime(int before_index, int after_index) {
5327  DCHECK(transition_time_);
5328  return transition_time_(before_index, after_index);
5329  }
5330 
5331 #if !defined(SWIG)
5332  virtual const std::vector<IntVar*>& nexts() const = 0;
5333  virtual const std::vector<IntVar*>& actives() const = 0;
5334  virtual const std::vector<IntVar*>& time_cumuls() const = 0;
5335  virtual const std::vector<IntVar*>& time_slacks() const = 0;
5336 #endif
5337 
5338  protected:
5339  const std::vector<IntervalVar*> intervals_;
5340  Solver::IndexEvaluator2 transition_time_;
5341 
5342  private:
5343  DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(DisjunctiveConstraint);
5344 };
5345 
5346 // ----- SolutionPool -----
5347 
5348 // This class is used to manage a pool of solutions. It can transform
5349 // a single point local search into a multipoint local search.
5350 class SolutionPool : public BaseObject {
5351  public:
5352  SolutionPool() {}
5353  ~SolutionPool() override {}
5354 
5355  // This method is called to initialize the solution pool with the assignment
5356  // from the local search.
5357  virtual void Initialize(Assignment* const assignment) = 0;
5358 
5359  // This method is called when a new solution has been accepted by the local
5360  // search.
5361  virtual void RegisterNewSolution(Assignment* const assignment) = 0;
5362 
5363  // This method is called when the local search starts a new neighborhood to
5364  // initialize the default assignment.
5365  virtual void GetNextSolution(Assignment* const assignment) = 0;
5366 
5367  // This method checks if the local solution needs to be updated with
5368  // an external one.
5369  virtual bool SyncNeeded(Assignment* const local_assignment) = 0;
5370 };
